Anglo American has announced the sale of the group’s remaining 8.0% shareholdingin Thungela Resources through an accelerated book build placing to a number ofmajor financial institutions, realising gross proceeds of approximately US$115 million. The Thungela shares were placed at a price of R154 per share, representing a 12% discount to the closing share price on 24 March 2022 and a 4% discount to the closing share price on 23 March 2022. RELATED:Proposed demerger of South Africa thermal coal operations approvedThungela posts solid results despite several challenges to operationsAnglo wraps up Thungela coal deal At the time of the demerger of Thungela to Anglo American’s shareholders, which completed in June 2021, Anglo American stated its intention to dispose of its remaining interest in Thungela over time and in a responsible manner, subject to market conditions and not within the first six months following the demerger. Following the end of that six month period in December 2021 and the end of Thungela’s closed period following the announcement of its 2021 results on 22 March 2022, Anglo American launched and completed the sale of its remaining shares and no longer holds any shares in Thungela. The Company has a primary listing on the Main Market of the London Stock Exchange and secondary listings on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange, the Botswana Stock Exchange, the Namibia Stock Exchange and the SIX Swiss Exchange.